The Index settles during bid week for the following month ( last week of Sep for Oct ) and is published around this time . This curve is probably in the system as basis , code D , which is the difference between the Index and NYMEX settle . This index is the Oct price curve ( P ) plus the Oct basis curve ( D) . Deals are +/- a few cents for The index ( I ) curve is next month's curve at what these differentials are trading at . It is not the actual "index" . It is what is added to the index for physical deals priced off index . I know it is confusing . Jason
